Description of incident: Sequoia Union High School District (SUHSD) notified employees and retiree personal information of a data breach when a phishing incident when a third party accessed an office computer that contained personal information of employees and retirees. The information compromised included names and Social Security numbers.The school district is providing a free membership for one year through ProtectMyID. For these questions they can call 1-844-754-5532 Monday through Friday 6:00 a.m to 6:00 p.m Pacific Time. More Information: http://oag.ca.gov/ecrime/databreach/reports/sb24-60445
